
                                            Officers traced the cables to a warehouse in Silverton, Tshwane.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Police have recovered half a million rands worth of copper cable stolen from City Power's Randburg station.  Officers traced the cables to a warehouse in Silverton, Tshwane.  Two men were arrested and two others are still at large.  The Public Safety Department's Luyanda Longwe said: “The two suspects have been charged with possession of stolen goods and are believed to have been working with other members. Police are still on the lookout for other suspects.”